content.problemStatement:
If A is an m x n matrix then A (Transpose of A) is an n x m matrix, such that rows of A become
columns of A and columns of A become rows of A .
Given a 2D array, you have to implement the given function,
int** Transpose(int** matrix, int rowCount, int columnCount);
int** Transpose(int** matrix, int rowCount, int columnCount);
static int[][] Transpose(int[][] matrix);
static int[,] Transpose(int[,] matrix);
def Transpose(matrix):
Implement the function to find the transpose of the matrix and return the new matrix as output.

